3. For every row in those columns, compute the total hours (`total_seconds / 3600`) and round up using `math.ceil`.
4. Overwrite the original cell with this integer and set its number format to General.
5. Save the workbook to the output directory with the same filename.
6. Call `recalculate` on the saved file, then reload with `data_only=True` to verify the results.
